		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;

 investment in available-for-sale securities

 and trade receivables approximate fair value due to their short maturities. The fair values of investment in available-for-sale securities are based on dealer quotes.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;3.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;FINANCIAL INSTRUMENTS&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;Certain financial assets and liabilities are accounted for at fair value
 which is defined as the price that would be received to sell an asset or paid to transfer a liability in an orderly transaction between market participants at the measurement date. The following fair value hierarchy prioritizes the inputs used to measure fair value: &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;Level 1 &amp;#x2013; Quoted prices are available in active markets for identical assets or liabilities as of the reporting date. Active markets are those in which transactions for the asset or liability occur in sufficient frequency and volume to provide pricing information on an ongoing basis. &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;Level 2 &amp;#x2013; Pricing inputs are other than quoted prices in active markets included in Level 1
 which are either directly or indirectly observable as of the reporting date. Level 2 includes those financial instruments that are valued using models or other valuation methodologies. &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;Level 3 &amp;#x2013; Pricing inputs include significant inputs that are generally less observable from objective sources. These inputs may be used with internally developed methodologies that result in management&amp;#x2019;s best estimate of fair value from the perspective of a market participant.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;The following table represents cash and the available-for-sale securities adjusted cost
 gross unrealized gains
 gross unrealized losses and fair value by significant investment category recorded as cash and cash equivalents or investment securities as of:&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;;font-size: 9pt&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 1pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;

				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:01.80%;border-top:1pt solid #000000 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1.5pt solid #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:34.50pt;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0.05pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;overflow: hidden;font-size:0pt;&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:07.98%;border-top:1pt solid #000000 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1.5pt solid #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:34.50pt;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0.05pt 0pt;text-align:center;font-family:Times New Roman;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;&gt;Unrealized Gains&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;The Company elected to early adopt pronouncement ASU 2015-17
 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-style:italic;&gt;Income Taxes (Topic 740): Balance Sheet Classification of Deferred Taxes&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;
 as of December 31
 2016 and applied its provisions retrospectively to each prior period presented for comparative purposes.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The provision requires the Company to classify all deferred tax assets and liabilities as noncurrent
 For the year&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;s&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; ended December 31
 2016&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;
 2015
 and 2014&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;
 the Company reclassified &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$1.7&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; million&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;
 &amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$1.2&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; million
 and &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$3.7&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; million
 respectively
&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; in current net deferred tax assets against the Company&amp;#x2019;s non-current deferred tax liability.&lt;/font&gt;

						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;

				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:07.24%;border-top:1pt solid #000000 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:2pt double #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:12.75pt;color:#000000;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;text-align:right; nowrap=nowrap&gt;10
664&amp;nbsp;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:02.04%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:12.75pt;padding:0pt;&gt;

		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt 0pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;


 the Company utilizes the single sales factor apportionment method in addition to claiming new state jobs credits and research &amp;amp; development credits.&amp;nbsp; In 2014 the Company benefited from research and development credits effective January 1
 2014 in addition to filing an amended federal return to claim 2010 research and development credits due to changes in Federal regulations.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;

		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  

		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;

 based on all available evidence
 management believes it is more-likely-than-not that the position will be sustained upon examination
 including the resolution of appeals or litigation processes
 if any. Tax positions taken are not offset or aggregated with other positions. Tax positions that meet the more-likely-than-not recognition threshold are measured as the largest amount of tax benefit that is more than 50 percent likely of being realized upon settlement with the applicable taxing authority. The portion of the benefits associated with tax positions taken that exceeds the amount measured as described above is reflected as a liability for unrecognized tax benefits in the accompanying balance sheet along with any associated interest and penalties that would be payable to the taxing authorities upon examination.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;&gt;We evaluated our tax positions and determined that we did not have any material uncertain tax positions. Our policy is to recognize interest and penalties accrued on uncertain tax positions as part of income tax expense. For the years ending December 31
 2016 and 2015
 no material estimated interest or penalties were recognized for the uncertainty of certain tax positions. We file income tax returns in the United States
 Canada and various states jurisdictions.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We are no longer subject to U.S. federal
 state
 and local income tax examinations by tax authorities for the years before 2013.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;&gt;Deferred tax assets are recognized for deductible temporary differences and deferred tax liabilities are recognized for taxable temporary differences. Temporary differences are the differences between the reported amounts of assets and liabilities and their tax bases. Deferred tax assets are reduced by a valuation allowance when
 in the opinion of management
 it is more likely than not that some portion or all of the deferred tax assets will not be realized. Deferred tax assets and liabilities are adjusted for the effects of changes in tax laws and rates on the date of enactment.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

		&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;4.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;INVENTORIES&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;Inventories consist principally of packaged meal replacements held in the Company&amp;#x2019;s warehouses.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Inventory is stated at the lower of cost or market
 utilizing the first-in
 first-out method.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The cost of finished goods includes the cost of raw materials
 packaging supplies
 direct and indirect labor and other indirect manufacturing costs.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;On a quarterly basis
 management reviews inventory for unsalable or obsolete inventory.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;

		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 1pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

  
  
  
  

		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;Inventory - &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;Inventories consist principally of packaged meal replacements held in the Company&amp;#x2019;s warehouses.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Inventory is stated at the lower of cost or market
 utilizing the first-in
 first-out method.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The cost of finished goods includes the cost of raw materials
 packaging supplies
 direct and indirect labor and other indirect manufacturing costs.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;On a quarterly basis
 management reviews inventory for unsalable or obsolete inventory.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  

		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;Investment Securities &amp;#x2013;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;The Company&amp;#x2019;s investments consist of debt and equity securities classified as available-for-sale securities.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Available-for-sale securities are stated at fair value
 and unrealized holding gains and losses
 net of the related deferred tax effect
 are reported as a separate component of accumulated other comprehensive income in stockholders' equity.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Interest and dividends on marketable debt and equity securities are recognized in income when declared. Realized gains and losses
 including losses from declines in value of specific securities determined by management to be other-than-temporary
 if any
 are included in income. &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;Operating Leases -&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; Medifast&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; leases retail stores
 distribution facilities
 and office space under operating leases.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Many of our lease agreements contain tenant improvement allowances
 rent holidays
 rent escalation clauses
 and contingent rent provisions.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The Company recognizes incentives and minimum rental expenses on a straight-line basis over the terms of the leases.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We commence recording rent expense on the date of initial possession
 which is generally when we enter the space and begin to make improvements to properties for our intended use.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;For tenant improvement allowances and rent holidays
 we record a deferred rent liability on the consolidated balance sheets and amortize the deferred rent over the terms of the leases as reductions to rent expense on the consolidated statements of income.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;For scheduled rent escalation clauses during the lease terms or for rental payments commencing at a date other than the date of initial occupancy
 we record minimum rental expenses on a straight-line basis over the terms of the leases on the consolidated statements of income.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Several leases provide for contingent rents
 which are determined as a percentage of gross sales in excess of specified levels.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We record a contingent rent liability on the consolidated balance sheets and the corresponding rent expense when we determine achieving the specified levels is probable.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;;font-size: 9pt&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt 0pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;7.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;LEASES&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;Operating Leases:&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 18pt 6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;As of December 31
 2016
 the Company leases office space for corporate offices
 a distribution facility in Texas
 a raw materials warehouse in Maryland
 as well as &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;20&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; previously corporate-operated Medifast Weight Control Centers under lease terms ranging from &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;five&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; to &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;ten&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; years.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The 20 leases include &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;3&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; closed Centers and &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;17&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; leases for Centers that were sold to franchise partners during 2014 and entered into sublease agreements with the franchisees.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The Company accrued for the remaining lease obligations net of any sublease income in 2014
 see Note 11 for exit activity and clinic obligations.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Monthly payments under the Medifast Weight Control Centers leases range in price from &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$1
800&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; to &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$4
200&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The Company is additionally required to pay property taxes
 utilities
 insurance and other costs relating to the leased facilities.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 18pt 6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;The following table summarizes our future minimum rental and lease payments required under non-cancelable original lease terms in excess of one year as of December 31
 2016:&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt 18pt 0pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 1pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;

			&lt;tr&gt;

					&lt;p style=margin:0.05pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;height:1.00pt;overflow:hidden;font-size: 1pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:04.10%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:1.00pt;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0.05pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;height:1.00pt;overflow:hidden;font-size:0pt;&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:04.10%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:1.00pt;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0.05pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;height:1.00pt;overflow:hidden;font-size:0pt;&gt;

			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;We have considered all new accounting pronouncements and have concluded that there are no new pronouncements that may have a material impact on our results of operations
 financial condition
 or cash flows
 based on current information
 except for:&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;ASU 2016-09
 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-style:italic;&gt;Compensation- Stock Compensation (Topic 718): Improvements to Employee Share-Based Payable Accounting&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; allows for the simplification of accounting for stock compensation in relation to income taxes
 classification of awards as equity or liabilities and classification on the statement of cash flows.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The pronouncement is effective for fiscal years beginning after December 15
 2016.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;Management has evaluated the pronouncement and determined that it will not have a material impact on the Company&amp;#x2019;s financial statements.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;ASU 2016-02
 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-style:italic;&gt;Leases (Topic 842)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; requires the rights and obligations of all leased assets with a term greater than 12 months to be presented on the balance sheet.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The pronouncement is effective for fiscal years beginning after December 15
 2018.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Management is currently evaluating the effect that the provisions of ASU 2016-02 will have on the Company&amp;#x2019;s financial statements.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;ASU 2016-01
 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-style:italic;&gt;Financial Instruments- Overall (Subtopic 825-10): Recognition and Measurement of Financial Assets and Financial Liabilities&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;
 most notably requires the changes in fair value of equity investments to be recognized in net income.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The pronouncement also requires the use of the exit price notion
 the separate presentation of financial assets and liabilities by measurement category and form of asset
 and the separate presentation in other comprehensive income of changes in fair value resulting from a change in the instrument-specific credit risk.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The pronouncement is effective for fiscal years beginning after December 15
 2017.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Based on the risk level of the Company&amp;#x2019;s investment portfolio
 Management does not expect the pronouncement to have a material impact on the Company&amp;#x2019;s financial statements.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;ASU 2015-11
 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-style:italic;&gt;Inventory (Topic 330): Simplifying the Measurement of Inventory&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;
 requires the Company to recognize inventory at the lower of cost and net realizable value.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Net realizable value is defined as the estimated selling price in the ordinary course of business less costs of completion
 disposal
 and transportation.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The pronouncement is effective for fiscal years beginning after December 31
 2016.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;Management has evaluated the pronouncement and determined that &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;it will not&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; have a material impact on the Company&amp;#x2019;s financial statements.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-style:italic;&gt;ASU 2015-09
 Revenue from Contracts with Customers (Topic 606)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;
 requires the Company to recognize revenue for the transfer of goods or services to customers for the amount the Company expects to be entitled to in exchange for those goods or services.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The Company will be required to identify the contract
 identify the relevant performance obligations
 determine the transaction price
 allocate the transaction price to the performance obligations in the contract
 and recognize the revenue when the entity satisfies a performance obligation.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The provisions of this ASU are effective for interim and annual periods beginning after December 15
 2017.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Management is &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;evaluating the effect that the provisions of ASU 2015-09 will have on the Company&amp;#x2019;s financial statements&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

 2016
 2015 and 2014 was &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$5.4 million&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;
 &amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$7.1 million&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;
 and &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$8.1 million&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;
 respectively.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The Company did not incur &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;any&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; depreciation and amortization expense for discontinued operations related to the Medifast Corporate Weight Control Centers for the years ended December 31
 2016 and 2015
 and incurred &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$1.7&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; million for the year ended December 31

 the Company incurred an asset impairment loss of &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$3.3&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; million in 2014 that is included in discontinued operations.&lt;/font&gt;

		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt 0pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;

		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;&gt;The depreciation life for leasehold improvements is the lesser of the estimated useful life of the addition or the term of the related lease.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:12pt 0pt 6pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;Long-lived assets are reviewed for impairment whenever events or changes in circumstances indicate that the carrying amount of an asset may not be recoverable. Recoverability of assets to be held and used is measured by a comparison of the carrying amount of an asset to estimated undiscounted future cash flows expected to be generated by the asset. If the carrying amount of an asset exceeds its estimated future cash flows
 an impairment charge is recognized by the amount by which the carrying amount of the asset exceeds the fair value of the asset. &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

 plant
 and equipment consisted of the following as of:&lt;/font&gt;

					&lt;p style=margin:0.05pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;height:1.00pt;overflow:hidden;font-size: 1pt&gt;

			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;Research and Development- &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;The Company incurs research and development costs in connection with the development of new products and programs
 which are expensed as incurred.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The Company also invests in studies to evaluate the effectiveness of our products and programs
 the costs of which are recognized evenly over the duration of the study.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The Company incurred &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$2.0&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; million
 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$1.8&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; million
 and &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$1.3&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; million in research and development expense for the years ended December 31
 2016
 2015
 and 2014
 respectively. &lt;/font&gt;

			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;During the first quarter of 2016
 the Company announced the departure of three Executive Vice Presidents in an effort to re-align the senior leadership team to reflect the changing needs of the business and to provide greater emphasis on the Company&amp;#x2019;s key areas of focus
 and also the resignation of the Company&amp;#x2019;s President and Chief Operating Officer.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The Company incurred &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$1.2&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; million in net restructuring costs in selling
 general
 and administrative expense associated with the departure of these four executives.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;This includes a &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$0.2&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; million reversal of costs accrued in 2015 for deferred shares that were granted in connection with the 2015 bonus plan and were forfeited as a result of their departure.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;

			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;10.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;BUSINESS SEGMENTS&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;

		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;Operating segments are components of an enterprise about which separate financial information is available that is regularly reviewed by the chief operating decision maker about how to allocate resources and in assessing performance.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The consolidated operating profit of the Company is reviewed by the chief operating decision maker as a single segment and sales are reviewed at the business unit level.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;

				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:03.46%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:12.75pt;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0.05pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;overflow: hidden;font-size:0pt;&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:03.46%;border-top:1pt solid #000000 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:2pt double #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:12.75pt;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0.05pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;color:#000000;&gt;$&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:19.16%;border-top:1pt solid #000000 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:2pt double #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:12.75pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;text-align:right; nowrap=nowrap&gt;274
534&amp;nbsp;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:01.82%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:12.75pt;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0.05pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;overflow: hidden;font-size:0pt;&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:03.46%;border-top:1pt solid #000000 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:2pt double #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:12.75pt;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0.05pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;color:#000000;&gt;$&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:19.16%;border-top:1pt solid #000000 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:2pt double #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:12.75pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;text-align:right; nowrap=nowrap&gt;272
773&amp;nbsp;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:01.82%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:12.75pt;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0.05pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;overflow: hidden;font-size:0pt;&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:03.46%;border-top:1pt solid #000000 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:2pt double #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:12.75pt;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0.05pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;color:#000000;&gt;$&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:19.16%;border-top:1pt solid #000000 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:2pt double #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:12.75pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;text-align:right; nowrap=nowrap&gt;285
285&amp;nbsp;
				&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 1pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  

		&lt;p style=margin:4.5pt 0pt 6pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;Share-Based Compensation - &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;Share-based&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; compensation consists primarily of restricted stock awards
 market- and performance-based share awards
 and &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;stock &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;options granted to employees and directors.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Restricted stock awards are measured at the grant date
 based on the calculated fair value of the award
 and are recognized as an expense over the requisite service period.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The fair value of the incentive stock options and non-qualified stock options is calculated using the Black-Scholes option pricing model as of the grant date and recognized over the service period.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Market and performance-based share awards that are tied to the Company&amp;#x2019;s total shareholder return and stock price are valued using the Monte Carlo method and are recognized as expense over the award&amp;#x2019;s achievement period.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The Company issues new shares upon the exercise of stock options and the granting of restricted stock awards.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

  
  
  
  
  
  

		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;Shipping and Handling Costs &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;- Our shipping and handling costs for shipments of our product to our customers are included in cost of sales. All shipping and handling charges that are billed to customers are included in net revenue. All other shipping and handling costs are included in selling
 general and administration expenses. &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

  
  

		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:9pt;&gt;2.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;SUMMARY OF SIGNIFICANT ACCOUNTING POLICIES&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;&gt;Significant accounting policies followed in the preparation of the consolidated financial statements are as follows:&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;

 Jason Pharmaceuticals
 Inc.
 Take Shape For Life
 LLC
 Seven Crondall Associates
 LLC
 Jason Properties
 LLC
 Medifast Franchise Systems
 Inc.
 Medifast Nutrition
 Inc.
 Optavia LLC
 Performance Products LLC
 and Jason Enterprises
 Inc. All inter-Company transactions and balances have been eliminated in consolidation. &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;

		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;

		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;

 institutional money funds and other short-term investments with a maturity of 90 days or less at the time of purchase. &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;

 and the balances with these financial institutions often exceed the amount of insurance provided on such accounts by the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation. The cash and cash equivalents generally are maintained with financial institutions with reputable credit
 and therefore bear minimal credit risk. Historically
 we have not experienced any losses due to such concentration of credit risk. &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;

 investment in available-for-sale securities

 and trade receivables approximate fair value due to their short maturities. The fair values of investment in available-for-sale securities are based on dealer quotes.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;Accounts Receivable and Allowance for Sales Returns and Doubtful Accounts - &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;Accounts receivable are recorded net of reserves for sales returns and allowances
 and net of provisions for doubtful accounts.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;We review the reserves for customer returns at each reporting period and adjust them to reflect data available at that time. To estimate reserves for returns
 we consider actual return rates in preceding periods. To the extent the estimate of returns changes
 we will adjust the reserve
 which will impact the amount of product sales revenue recognized in the period of the adjustment. Our estimates for returns have not differed materially from our actual returns. The provision for estimated returns as of December 31
 2016 and 2015 was &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$394
000&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; and &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$323
000&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;
 respectively.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;Allowances for doubtful accounts are based primarily on an analysis of aged accounts receivable balances and the credit worthiness of our customers as determined by credit checks and analysis
 as well as customer payment history.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The allowance for doubtful accounts as of December 31
 2016 and 2015 was &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$55
000&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; and &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$94
000&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;
 respectively.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;Inventory - &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;Inventories consist principally of packaged meal replacements held in the Company&amp;#x2019;s warehouses.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Inventory is stated at the lower of cost or market
 utilizing the first-in
 first-out method.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The cost of finished goods includes the cost of raw materials
 packaging supplies
 direct and indirect labor and other indirect manufacturing costs.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;On a quarterly basis
 management reviews inventory for unsalable or obsolete inventory.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;Investment Securities &amp;#x2013;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;The Company&amp;#x2019;s investments consist of debt and equity securities classified as available-for-sale securities.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Available-for-sale securities are stated at fair value
 and unrealized holding gains and losses
 net of the related deferred tax effect
 are reported as a separate component of accumulated other comprehensive income in stockholders' equity.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Interest and dividends on marketable debt and equity securities are recognized in income when declared. Realized gains and losses
 including losses from declines in value of specific securities determined by management to be other-than-temporary
 if any
 are included in income. &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;

 based on all available evidence
 management believes it is more-likely-than-not that the position will be sustained upon examination
 including the resolution of appeals or litigation processes
 if any. Tax positions taken are not offset or aggregated with other positions. Tax positions that meet the more-likely-than-not recognition threshold are measured as the largest amount of tax benefit that is more than 50 percent likely of being realized upon settlement with the applicable taxing authority. The portion of the benefits associated with tax positions taken that exceeds the amount measured as described above is reflected as a liability for unrecognized tax benefits in the accompanying balance sheet along with any associated interest and penalties that would be payable to the taxing authorities upon examination.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;&gt;We evaluated our tax positions and determined that we did not have any material uncertain tax positions. Our policy is to recognize interest and penalties accrued on uncertain tax positions as part of income tax expense. For the years ending December 31
 2016 and 2015
 no material estimated interest or penalties were recognized for the uncertainty of certain tax positions. We file income tax returns in the United States
 Canada and various states jurisdictions.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We are no longer subject to U.S. federal
 state
 and local income tax examinations by tax authorities for the years before 2013.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;&gt;Deferred tax assets are recognized for deductible temporary differences and deferred tax liabilities are recognized for taxable temporary differences. Temporary differences are the differences between the reported amounts of assets and liabilities and their tax bases. Deferred tax assets are reduced by a valuation allowance when
 in the opinion of management
 it is more likely than not that some portion or all of the deferred tax assets will not be realized. Deferred tax assets and liabilities are adjusted for the effects of changes in tax laws and rates on the date of enactment.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;

 except for the preparation
 layout
 design and production of advertising costs which are expensed when the advertisement is first used.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Advertising expense for continuing operations
 excluding broker fees
 for the years ended December 31
 2016
 2015
 and 2014



 respectively.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;Operating Leases -&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; Medifast&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; leases retail stores
 distribution facilities
 and office space under operating leases.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Many of our lease agreements contain tenant improvement allowances
 rent holidays
 rent escalation clauses
 and contingent rent provisions.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The Company recognizes incentives and minimum rental expenses on a straight-line basis over the terms of the leases.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We commence recording rent expense on the date of initial possession
 which is generally when we enter the space and begin to make improvements to properties for our intended use.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;For tenant improvement allowances and rent holidays
 we record a deferred rent liability on the consolidated balance sheets and amortize the deferred rent over the terms of the leases as reductions to rent expense on the consolidated statements of income.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;For scheduled rent escalation clauses during the lease terms or for rental payments commencing at a date other than the date of initial occupancy
 we record minimum rental expenses on a straight-line basis over the terms of the leases on the consolidated statements of income.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Several leases provide for contingent rents
 which are determined as a percentage of gross sales in excess of specified levels.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We record a contingent rent liability on the consolidated balance sheets and the corresponding rent expense when we determine achieving the specified levels is probable.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;Clinic Closure Costs&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;- Clinic closure costs are expensed and recognized as a liability at their fair value when incurred.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;One-time employee severance costs are expensed and recognized as a liability when the plan is finalized by management
 approved and committed to by management
 and communicated to the employee.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Contractual costs that will continue to be incurred (operating leases) are recognized at the cease use date.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The fair value of operating lease contracts is determined based on the present value of the remaining lease payments.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Other costs associated with closing the clinic or relocating employees are expensed as incurred.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;Property
 Plant
 and Equipment - &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;Property
 plant and equipment are stated at cost less accumulated depreciation and amortization. The Company computes depreciation and amortization using the straight-line method over the estimated useful lives of the assets acquired as follows:&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 1pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;div style=width:100%&gt;&lt;table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 style=border-collapse:collapse;width: 60.00%;margin-left:0pt;&gt;
			&lt;tr&gt;
				&lt;td valign=middle style=width:58.50%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:1.00pt;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0.05pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;height:1.00pt;overflow:hidden;font-size: 1pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=middle style=width:04.98%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:1.00pt;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0.05pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;height:1.00pt;overflow:hidden;font-size:0pt;&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=middle style=width:03.86%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:1.00pt;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0.05pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;height:1.00pt;overflow:hidden;font-size:0pt;&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=middle style=width:32.66%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:1.00pt;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0.05pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;height:1.00pt;overflow:hidden;font-size:0pt;&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;tr&gt;
				&lt;td valign=middle style=width:58.50%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:12.75pt;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0.05pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 10pt&gt;
						&lt;font style=display: inline;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;&gt;Building and building improvements&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=middle style=width:04.98%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:12.75pt;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0.05pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;overflow: hidden;font-size:0pt;&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=middle style=width:03.86%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #auto;height:12.75pt;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0.05pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;overflow: hidden;font-size:0pt;&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;

		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt 0pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;&gt;The depreciation life for leasehold improvements is the lesser of the estimated useful life of the addition or the term of the related lease.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:12pt 0pt 6pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;Long-lived assets are reviewed for impairment whenever events or changes in circumstances indicate that the carrying amount of an asset may not be recoverable. Recoverability of assets to be held and used is measured by a comparison of the carrying amount of an asset to estimated undiscounted future cash flows expected to be generated by the asset. If the carrying amount of an asset exceeds its estimated future cash flows
 an impairment charge is recognized by the amount by which the carrying amount of the asset exceeds the fair value of the asset. &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:12pt 0pt 6pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;Research and Development- &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;The Company incurs research and development costs in connection with the development of new products and programs
 which are expensed as incurred.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The Company also invests in studies to evaluate the effectiveness of our products and programs
 the costs of which are recognized evenly over the duration of the study.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The Company incurred &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$2.0&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; million
 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$1.8&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; million
 and &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;$1.3&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; million in research and development expense for the years ended December 31
 2016
 2015
 and 2014
 respectively. &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;

 rebates
 promotional adjustments
 price adjustments
 and estimated returns and upon transfer of title and risk to the customer which occurs at shipping (F.O.B. terms).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Upon shipment
 the Company has no further performance obligations and collection is reasonably assured as the majority of sales are paid prior to shipping.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Medifast Weight Control Centers program fees were recognized over the estimated service period.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;Shipping and Handling Costs &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;- Our shipping and handling costs for shipments of our product to our customers are included in cost of sales. All shipping and handling charges that are billed to customers are included in net revenue. All other shipping and handling costs are included in selling
 general and administration expenses. &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;Earnings per Share &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;- &amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;Basic earnings per share (&amp;#x201C;EPS&amp;#x201D;) computations are calculated utilizing the weighted average number of shares of common stock outstanding during the periods presented.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Diluted EPS is calculated utilizing the weighted average number of shares of common stock outstanding adjusted for the effect of dilutive common stock equivalents.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;

		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 13.5pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:4.5pt 0pt 6pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;The calculation of diluted earnings per share excluded &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;35
000&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;
 &amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;69
375&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; and &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;67
375&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; antidilutive options outstanding for the years ended December 31
 2016
 2015
 and 2014 respectively.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The calculation of diluted earnings per share for the year ended December 31
 2016 also excluded &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;93&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; antidilutive restricted stock awards.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:4.5pt 0pt 6pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;Share-Based Compensation - &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;Share-based&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; compensation consists primarily of restricted stock awards
 market- and performance-based share awards
 and &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;stock &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;options granted to employees and directors.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Restricted stock awards are measured at the grant date
 based on the calculated fair value of the award
 and are recognized as an expense over the requisite service period.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The fair value of the incentive stock options and non-qualified stock options is calculated using the Black-Scholes option pricing model as of the grant date and recognized over the service period.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Market and performance-based share awards that are tied to the Company&amp;#x2019;s total shareholder return and stock price are valued using the Monte Carlo method and are recognized as expense over the award&amp;#x2019;s achievement period.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The Company issues new shares upon the exercise of stock options and the granting of restricted stock awards.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:4.5pt 0pt 6pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-weight:bold;&gt;Comprehensive Income - &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;Other comprehensive income refers to revenues
 expenses
 gains and losses that are not included in net income but rather are recorded directly in stockholders&amp;#x2019; equity. Comprehensive income consists of net income
 unrealized gains and losses on available-for-sale securities
 and foreign currency translation adjustments.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Courier New;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:9pt;&gt;Recent Accounting Pronouncements&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;We have considered all new accounting pronouncements and have concluded that there are no new pronouncements that may have a material impact on our results of operations
 financial condition
 or cash flows
 based on current information
 except for:&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;ASU 2016-09
 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-style:italic;&gt;Compensation- Stock Compensation (Topic 718): Improvements to Employee Share-Based Payable Accounting&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; allows for the simplification of accounting for stock compensation in relation to income taxes
 classification of awards as equity or liabilities and classification on the statement of cash flows.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The pronouncement is effective for fiscal years beginning after December 15
 2016.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;Management has evaluated the pronouncement and determined that it will not have a material impact on the Company&amp;#x2019;s financial statements.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;ASU 2016-02
 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-style:italic;&gt;Leases (Topic 842)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; requires the rights and obligations of all leased assets with a term greater than 12 months to be presented on the balance sheet.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The pronouncement is effective for fiscal years beginning after December 15
 2018.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Management is currently evaluating the effect that the provisions of ASU 2016-02 will have on the Company&amp;#x2019;s financial statements.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;ASU 2016-01
 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-style:italic;&gt;Financial Instruments- Overall (Subtopic 825-10): Recognition and Measurement of Financial Assets and Financial Liabilities&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;
 most notably requires the changes in fair value of equity investments to be recognized in net income.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The pronouncement also requires the use of the exit price notion
 the separate presentation of financial assets and liabilities by measurement category and form of asset
 and the separate presentation in other comprehensive income of changes in fair value resulting from a change in the instrument-specific credit risk.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The pronouncement is effective for fiscal years beginning after December 15
 2017.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Based on the risk level of the Company&amp;#x2019;s investment portfolio
 Management does not expect the pronouncement to have a material impact on the Company&amp;#x2019;s financial statements.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;ASU 2015-11
 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-style:italic;&gt;Inventory (Topic 330): Simplifying the Measurement of Inventory&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;
 requires the Company to recognize inventory at the lower of cost and net realizable value.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Net realizable value is defined as the estimated selling price in the ordinary course of business less costs of completion
 disposal
 and transportation.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The pronouncement is effective for fiscal years beginning after December 31
 2016.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;Management has evaluated the pronouncement and determined that &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;it will not&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt; have a material impact on the Company&amp;#x2019;s financial statements.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-style:italic;&gt;ASU 2015-09
 Revenue from Contracts with Customers (Topic 606)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;
 requires the Company to recognize revenue for the transfer of goods or services to customers for the amount the Company expects to be entitled to in exchange for those goods or services.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The Company will be required to identify the contract
 identify the relevant performance obligations
 determine the transaction price
 allocate the transaction price to the performance obligations in the contract
 and recognize the revenue when the entity satisfies a performance obligation.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The provisions of this ASU are effective for interim and annual periods beginning after December 15
 2017.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Management is &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;evaluating the effect that the provisions of ASU 2015-09 will have on the Company&amp;#x2019;s financial statements&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;&gt;.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=1&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  

		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;text-align:left;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;

		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt;text-align:left;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;

 2017&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;&gt;



 2017&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;&gt;.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:6pt 0pt 0pt;text-align:center;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Courier New;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size: 9pt&gt;
			&lt;font style=display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:9pt;&gt;&amp;#xFEFF;&lt;/font&gt;
